menu "breadboard: bb_wifi_http (STA /api/wifi + /api/scan route bundle)"

config BB_WIFI_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register /api/wifi and /api/scan HTTP routes via bb_init"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_wifi_http self-registers GET /api/wifi (driver state +
        connection diagnostics) and GET /api/scan (async scan results) through
        bb_init. The wifi driver init APIs (bb_wifi_init, _init_sta,
        _ensure_netif, etc.) stay caller-driven regardless of this flag.

        This flag was relocated from bb_wifi's Kconfig (PR1, KB 781) — the
        symbol name is unchanged so existing sdkconfig files keep working.
        Omit bb_wifi_http from your component graph entirely for a minimal
        STA-only image that doesn't pay the http/json/openapi heap cost.

endmenu
